import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def calculate_percent_nav(df, total_nav=None):
    if total_nav is None:
        total_nav = df["% of NAV"].sum()
    if len(df) == 1:
        return [df["% of NAV"].iloc[0]]
    else:
        nav = df["% of NAV"].iloc[0]
        percent = (nav / total_nav) * 100
        return [percent] + calculate_percent_nav(df.iloc[1:], total_nav)
df = pd.read_csv(r"C:\Users\Sofiyan\Desktop\learn-py\ALGO-PROJECT\index1.csv")

df['% of NAV'] = df['% of NAV'].str.rstrip('%').astype(float)

df = df.dropna(subset=['% of NAV'])

equity_names = df["Equity Name"]
percent_nav = df["% of NAV"]
#yahan par recusrively calculate karta uno
percentages = calculate_percent_nav(df)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.pie(percentages, labels=equity_names, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=5000, labeldistance=0.5, textprops={'fontsize': -1})

plt.title("Percentage of NAV by Equity AXIS BANK")
plt.axis('equal') 
plt.legend(equity_names, loc='lower right')

plt.show()
